{"key":"processedPost-12757856","value":{"id":12757856,"first":12757837,"last":12757890,"when":1276797962,"utime":"06/17/10 09:06 PM","cleanedPost":"Letting the cakes sit between flushes isn't related to contamination.&nbsp; It's to let the mycelium digest a bit more of the substrate before flushing again.&nbsp; However, many strains don't grow in nice, neat flushes.&nbsp; They produce a steady stream of fruits.&nbsp; <br />If you're going to let the cakes 'rest' between flushes, take them to a dry area and let them sit without misting for that duration.&nbsp; Then, soak overnight and return to fruiting conditions.<br />RR"}}